===Etymology===
From the [[Slavic]] suffix ({{etyl|ru|en}}: {{m|ru|-ник}}). This suffix experienced a surge in English coinages for nicknames and diminutives after the 1957 Soviet launch of the first [[w:Sputnik program|Sputnik satellite]]. English usage is heavily influenced by {{etyl|yi|en}} usage of {{m|yi|־ניק}} and similar borrowed words ([[nogoodnik]], [[nudnik]], [[kibbutznik]]).

===Suffix===
{{en-suffix}}

# {{n-g|Creates a [[nickname]] for a person who [[exemplify|exemplifies]], [[endorse]]s, or is associated with the thing or quality specified (by the base form), often a particular [[ideology]] or preference.}}

